    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have a function that I have been using to query the terminal pixels size with ioctl. \n\nI noticed today after updating nightly after calling \":restart\" the function stops working and instead errors. \n> assert(ffi.C.ioctl(1, TIOCGWINSZ, sz) == 0, 'Failed to get terminal size')\n> E5113: Lua chunk: ... Failed to get terminal size                                                                                                                                                  \n\nIt seems to be occurring after this change a few days ago, however at this point it simply fails silently on restart:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35223\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Copy the snippet below to a file called `init.lua`\n2. Run it with: `nvim --clean -u /path/to/init.lua`\n3. At startup it will print the terminal sizes (you may need to hit enter to continue)\n4. After 5 seconds it will call `:restart`  \n5. Upon restarting an error will display similar to:\n    > E5113: Lua chunk: ... Failed to get terminal size                                                                                                                                                            \n    > stack traceback: ... [C]: in function 'assert'               \n\n\n```lua\n                                                                                                                                                                                   \n-- I copied this a few years ago from: `https://github.com/edluffy/hologram.nvim/blob/main/lua/hologram/state.lua#L15`\nfunction query_term_size()\n  local ffi = require('ffi')\n  ffi.cdef([[\n  typedef struct {\n    unsigned short row;\n    unsigned short col;\n    unsigned short xpixel;\n    unsigned short ypixel;\n  } winsize;\n  int ioctl(int, int, ...);\n  ]])\n\n  local TIOCGWINSZ = nil\n  if vim.fn.has('linux') == 1 then\n    TIOCGWINSZ = 0x5413\n  elseif vim.fn.has('mac') == 1 then\n    TIOCGWINSZ = 0x40087468\n  elseif vim.fn.has('bsd') == 1 then\n    TIOCGWINSZ = 0x40087468\n  end\n\n  ---@type { row: number, col: number, xpixel: number, ypixel: number }\n  local sz = ffi.new('winsize')\n  assert(ffi.C.ioctl(1, TIOCGWINSZ, sz) == 0, 'Failed to get terminal size')\n\n  return {\n    rows = sz.row,\n    cols = sz.col,\n    pixel_width = sz.xpixel,\n    pixel_height = sz.ypixel,\n    cell_pixel_width = sz.xpixel / sz.col,\n    cell_pixel_height = sz.ypixel / sz.row,\n  }\nend\n\nprint(vim.inspect(query_term_size()))\n\nprint('Restarting in 5 seconds')\n\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  vim.cmd.restart()\nend, 5000)\n\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShould be able to query the terminal sizes after calling restart.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-60+g3cb79189f3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04.4 LTS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.46.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage nightly",
